    "body": "If I recall correctly, metadata plugins end up called by the C core, potentially asynchronously.\r\n\r\nIt's possible that we could wrap the metadata plugins with a fresh object + try/except that sets a stateful flag and pedantically check that flag for every object that transitively touches that wrapper."
