    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "> Alternatively we can document that users should do that themselves and do failure-callbacks of some kind. But then I don't know how able they'd be to kill off gRPC resources from outside of the library proper.\r\n\r\nI'm not intimately familiar with gRPC's implementation or error handling, but I don't feel like users should need to do anything else for errors from metadata plugins to propagate.\r\n\r\nEven if gRPC raises a *different* error when making an RPC where the metadata plugin raises an error that's still better than what happens now (the application hangs)."
